Editing the sprint field to have a random string will produce a NumberFormatException
Editing the sprint field to have a number that isn't the id of a sprint will produce a NullPointerException

This affects Bonfire as users would expect the field to accept values.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-5261].
  {panel}

- When trying to choose from one of the Boards we have setup, Greenhopper doesn't bring up any Board other than Default.

- Have to manually enter the following code (using cntrl-shift-j) - as an example when I want to bring up our Epics Board, I have to enter the following code each time I wish display it: Boards.setCtx('Epics@!@rick').

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-5212].
  {panel}

In the current planning board when you have a story and sub-tasks, all of the numbers total up to the story Estimated Time Remaining.  Markers can then be used to plan the sprints. 

When I go over to the new Rapid Board the sub tasks are not counted when I plan my project.  If I have put all my estimates against the sub tasks the story shows up as a zero time item in the story when planning.  If I manually sum up the tasks and put the number on the story then it messes up my metrics.

*Rating*: :) Good

{panel:title=What do you like?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#c2ffa2|bgColor=#fff}
I like your way to improve planning activity (and not only planning) with Rapid Boards.
{panel}

